The paper deals with scheduling algorithms for multiprocessors, which is a topic in the field of distributed systems (cs.DS). The focus is on optimizing energy consumption, which is a common concern in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of performance metrics, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The scheduling algorithms need to make decisions based on the current state of the system, which involves control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents lower bounds on the competitive ratio of the algorithms, which is a topic in the field of performance analysis (cs.PF).
